    "type": "technique",
    "category": "techniques",
    "title": "Jammy egg",
    "desc": "Boil a fridge-cold large egg for 6 minutes 30 seconds, ice-shock immediately. The white sets fully (62 to 70 °C internal); the yolk holds at the chalky-cream threshold (about 68 °C): set enough to hold a dome at the cut, soft enough to weep slightly when broken.",
